
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `add-apt-repository` baraye ezafe kardane yek manba’ jadid (repository) be list-e manabe’ APT shoma estefade mishavad. APT barname-i ast baraye nasb va modiriyat-e narmafzar dar Debian va Ubuntu. Ba ezafe kardane repository-haye jadid, shoma mitavanid narmafzar-haye bishtari ra nasb konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `add-apt-repository ppa:<esm-e-ppa>`  --> ➕ Ezafe kardane yek PPA (Personal Package Archive). PPA-ha repository-haye shakhsi hastand ke barname-haye jadid ya version-haye jadidtari az barname-haye mojood ra dar khod jaay dahand. Mesal: `sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php`
    🔹 `add-apt-repository --remove ppa:<esm-e-ppa>` --> ➖ Hazf kardane yek PPA. Mesal: `sudo add-apt-repository --remove ppa:ondrej/php`
    🔹 `add-apt-repository <line-e-manba’>` --> 📝 Ezafe kardane yek line-e manba’ mostaghim az tarigh-e command line. In ravesh baraye repository-haye gheir-PPA estefade mishavad. Mesal: `sudo add-apt-repository "deb http://example.com/ubuntu bionic main"`

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:libreoffice/ppa

    🔹 Ezafe kardane PPA rasmi LibreOffice baraye daryaft-e akharin version-e LibreOffice.

    $ sudo add-apt-repository --remove ppa:libreoffice/ppa

    🔹 Hazf kardane PPA rasmi LibreOffice.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:wireshark/stable
    $ sudo apt update

    🔹 Ebtedaa, PPA Wireshark (baraye tool analizi network) ezafe mishavad. Seepas, `apt update` ejra mishavad ta list-e package-ha az hameye repository-haye mojood, az jomle PPA jadid, be rooz shavad. Ba’d az aan, shoma mitavanid Wireshark ra az tarigh-e `apt install wireshark` nasb konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `add-apt-repository` command is used to add a new repository to your APT source list. APT is a package management system used on Debian and Ubuntu systems for installing and managing software. By adding new repositories, you can install more software packages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `add-apt-repository ppa:<ppa-name>` --> ➕ Adds a PPA (Personal Package Archive). PPAs are personal repositories that contain new programs or newer versions of existing programs. Example: `sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php`
    🔹 `add-apt-repository --remove ppa:<ppa-name>` --> ➖ Removes a PPA. Example: `sudo add-apt-repository --remove ppa:ondrej/php`
    🔹 `add-apt-repository <source-line>` --> 📝 Adds a direct source line via the command line. This is used for non-PPA repositories. Example: `sudo add-apt-repository "deb http://example.com/ubuntu bionic main"`

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:libreoffice/ppa

    🔹 Adds the official LibreOffice PPA to get the latest versions of LibreOffice.

    $ sudo add-apt-repository --remove ppa:libreoffice/ppa

    🔹 Removes the official LibreOffice PPA.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:wireshark/stable
    $ sudo apt update

    🔹 First, the Wireshark PPA (for network analysis tool) is added. Then, `apt update` is run to refresh the package list from all repositories, including the new PPA. After that, you can install Wireshark using `apt install wireshark`.
